{"questionId":"11879","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{2{x^2} - 5x - 12}}{{x + 2}}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,x \\in \\mathbb{R}{\\text{,}}\\,\\,x \\ne&nbsp; - 2\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>12</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>∈</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>≠</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the equation of the vertical asymptote.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x =&nbsp; - 2\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11879","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.5b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Write down the equation of the vertical asymptote.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.13—Rational functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}